{
  "info": {
    "name": "Socket Chat (Socket.IO) Flow",
    "_postman_id": "2a5f6f2b-27f6-4e5b-9db7-1c8f9e47c9e8",
    "description": "End-to-end setup for Socket.IO chat testing.\n\nHow to use in Postman:\n- Import this collection and the environment `Socket Chat Local`.\n- Run the two HTTP requests to register users and capture tokens.\n- Create a **Socket.IO** request in Postman (New → Socket.IO) and connect to `{{socketUrl}}`.\n- In the Socket.IO request's **Auth** (handshake auth) set: `{ \"token\": \"Bearer {{userAToken}}\" }`.\n  - This matches the server's socket auth logic: it reads `socket.handshake.auth.token` or `authorization` header.\n- Add listeners:\n  - `chat:message` (incoming message)\n  - `chat:read:update` (read receipts)\n- Send events:\n  - `chat:send` with `{ \"recipientUserId\": \"{{userBId}}\", \"content\": \"hello\" }`\n  - `chat:read` with `{ \"messageId\": \"<paste messageId here>\" }`\n\nNotes:\n- This backend uses Socket.IO over WebSockets. Postman doesn't support long-polling fallback.\n- The server joins each authenticated user to a room `user:<userId>` and emits `chat:message` to both sender + recipient.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1) Register User A (Mentor)",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"socket-user-a@test.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Password123\",\n  \"firstName\": \"Socket\",\n  \"lastName\": \"UserA\",\n  \"role\": \"MENTOR\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/register",
          "host": [
            "{{baseUrl}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "v1",
            "auth",
            "register"
          ]
        }
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Register user A success', function () {",
              "  pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
              "});",
              "const json = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.environment.set('userAToken', json.data.accessToken);",
              "pm.environment.set('userAId', json.data.user.userId);"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "2) Register User B (Learner)",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"socket-user-b@test.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Password123\",\n  \"firstName\": \"Socket\",\n  \"lastName\": \"UserB\",\n  \"role\": \"LEARNER\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/register",
          "host": [
            "{{baseUrl}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "v1",
            "auth",
            "register"
          ]
        }
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Register user B success', function () {",
              "  pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
              "});",
              "const json = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.environment.set('userBToken', json.data.accessToken);",
              "pm.environment.set('userBId', json.data.user.userId);"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "3) Get Conversation (HTTP fallback)",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Authorization",
            "value": "Bearer {{userAToken}}"
          }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/messages/with/{{userBId}}",
          "host": [
            "{{baseUrl}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "v1",
            "messages",
            "with",
            "{{userBId}}"
          ]
        }
      }
    }
  ],
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:5000"
    },
    {
      "key": "socketUrl",
      "value": "ws://localhost:5000"
    }
  ]
}
